mxCell.value:
Eventual Consistency Mitigator

With this component we can quickly provide inline data changes to the front. Increasing the level of experience.

There are three main options:

  1. Notify only changed data: The front will update only such data
  2. Notify data change: The front will refresh the whole view sending a new full request
  3. Combination of both based on the scenario

Eventual Consistency

When new transactions are done theres is a lack of time where the data viewed or returned to the consumers might not be the latest but soon or later it will be.

mxCell.value:
View Repos

The data might be semi-structured depending on the channel

The data views should be like final user will see to avoid transformations or adaptions that increase the delay into visualize the data

Internally, there mustn't bee any dependency between Views fo different channels

Open Points

  • API Authorization Layer
  • RO Reader API per Channel or one for all
  • Anticorruption layer includes Domain Brokers or not
  • AWS resources cost segregation for NDC?
  • Decision about EC Mitigator approach
  • RO Database with data triggers for manual
  • RO View Builder for existing data when you change the requirements of your views
  • Change Compoanent by Containers at Writer Layers
  • Add new Component for the transaction which will update the DB, then send the event and if anything failures to Error Processing Component as per Google Wallet
  • ACL AWS account allocation per Domain?

View Builders

In order to give full flexibility and meet different kind of requirments, roadmaps or UX experiences in general, we propose to split the view builders by dufferent components to avoid regresion tests, capacity, deployments or sevrice interruptions

RO DB

The data must be structured to ensure integrity and consistency

It will be the Golden Source for Retrieve Order information. Any data to be shared with other domains should be taken from here

It also allows to regenerate views in case of DR, Initial Load, New Releases, etc.. by using Outbox Pattern

Transactions are Out of Scope

Any transaction related to the Data Views is Out of the scope of this solution.

It is assumed it will be managed per existing services/systems

RO Data Writers

The additional split per entity follwos the Separation of Concerns principle

 for having each DataWriter per Entity is to reduce the dependency, the data availability, allowing the evolution, implementation and validation per each on a fully autonomous way. Regression tests are aonly required for a very sepcifc set of fucntionaities and components reducing drastically the time-to-market

The subscription by the queue to the Publisher is done through Event Bridge Product Container, not represented as it is part of the Reference Architecture

ACL Data Publishers

is a protective layer that sits between different subsystems or bounded contexts, ensuring that their inner models and logic don't corrupt one another, basically between the OnPrem and Legacy implmentations from the future ToBe with the whole rearchitecture.

The additional split per entity follwos the Separation of Concerns principle, 

having each DataWriter per Entity is to reduce the dependency, the data availability, allowing the evolution, implementation and validation per each on a fully autonomous way. Regression tests are aonly required for a very sepcifc set of fucntionaities and components reducing drastically the time-to-market

The publishing by the queue to the Subscribers is done through Event Bridge Product Container, not represented as it is part of the Reference Architecture

The subscription by the queue to the Publisher is done through Event Bridge Product Container, not represented as it is part of the Reference Architecture
